record_data.record_title: Schuylkill Energy Resources, Inc. FERC Elec Tariff Vol No 1
record_data.record_plain_text:
Schuylkill Energy Resources, Inc. FERC Electric Tariff, Volume No. 1 Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service Schuylkill Energy Resources, Inc. ("SER") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from its generating facility located in Mahanoy Township, Pennsylvania and interconnected to transmission facilities of PPL Electric Utilities Corporation. This FERC Electric Tariff, Original Volume No. 2 sets forth SER's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Supply Service to PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"), as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff.
SER's monthly revenue requirement consists of the sum of the charges for the Fixed Capability Revenue Requirement and Heating Losses Revenue Requirement. Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Tariff shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
1. FIXED CAPABILITY COMPONENT
The annual revenue requirement for the Fixed Capability Component is $641,465. The monthly charge to PJM is $641,465 / 12 = $53,455.
2. HEATING LOSSES COMPONENT
The annual revenue requirement for the Heating Losses Component is $201,746. The monthly charge to PJM is $201,746 / 12 = $16,812.
3. TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT
The total annual revenue requirement is $641,465 + $201,746 = $843,211. The total monthly revenue requirement is $843,211 / 12 = $70,267.
4. EFFECTIVE: January 1, 2011
